No Pulumi stack credentials available in this worktree, so `dotnet build` serves as evidence. Zero warnings, zero errors.

### Changes Made
- Extracted 9 Cosmos DB container definitions from ~218 lines of repetitive `SqlResourceSqlContainer` constructors into a `CosmosContainerDefinition` record + `foreach` loop
- `CosmosContainerDefinition` is a sealed record with: `Name`, `PartitionKeyPath`, optional `DefaultTtl`, optional `UniqueKeyPaths`, optional `IndexingPolicy`
- The loop constructs identical `SqlResourceSqlContainer` resources with identical logical names (`container-{name.ToLowerInvariant()}-{env}`)
- File reduced from 452 to 358 lines (~21% total reduction; ~49% reduction in the container section)

### Zero-Diff Guarantee
All 9 Pulumi resource logical names are preserved exactly:
- container-applications-{env}
- container-users-{env}
- container-watchzones-{env}
- container-notifications-{env}
- container-leases-{env}
- container-deviceregistrations-{env}
- container-savedapplications-{env}
- container-groups-{env}
- container-decisionalerts-{env}

All resource properties (ContainerName, PartitionKey, DefaultTtl, UniqueKeyPolicy, IndexingPolicy) are preserved identically.

### Configuration
No new Pulumi config values required. This is a pure code refactor.
